    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University Hospital, Angers</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Blood activation induced by cardiopulmonary bypass may compromise the postoperative outcome.
      The goal of this study is to compare blood activation induced by cardiopulmonary bypass
      performed with centrifugal pump or roller pump in patients undergoing coronary artery
      surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
